The paper deals with privacy-preserving algorithms in distributed computation, which is a topic that falls under the categories of cryptography (cs.CR) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The paper also involves information theory (cs.IT) in terms of analyzing the privacy guarantees of the algorithms. The algorithms are designed to be used in consensus-based distributed computation or optimization, which falls under the category of control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper involves analyzing the convergence of the algorithms, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG).
